&quot;So Seani, it's ok if your guildmates do this to other people, as long as they don't do it to TWC...because that would get them removed.&quot; -- You're oversimplifying a rather complex issue.<br>
<br>
First of all as I said earlier, the relationship between the two guilds involved matters.  If the guilds involved aren't in competition then personally I have no problem as a guild leader with people sharing their account info.  If they are in competition, ideally there is no sharing whatsoever.  Reality says that RL family and friendships and other close relationships trump artificial social rules imposed in a video game -- they'll share their account access no matter what you say.  <br>
<br>
So when they do share info, how you're found out is what matters.  If no trouble is caused and they dont tell you they're sharing, then there is really no point in even thinking about the issue.<br>
<br>
If ToN knows which of their members has given their account info to someone in TWC and you feel it is an issue (enough have a problem with this sort of thing), like I said, I recommend you boot that person(s) out of your guild until they promise not to do it or whatever you feel is appropriate.  Realistically that promise is for shit, but we can all pretend until it is evident that they've made a liar out of themselves and you still think its important.<br>
<br>
Then again, if the worst thing that happened here is that someone sent your members tells repeating back your /gu or motd, then like I said /ignore and you can go back to pretending they dont have access and everything is still cool in EQ land.  So far that's the worst thing that has evidently happened.<br>
<br>
I want to know why names still havent been named.  What are you afraid of?<br>
